1. Loading the package

pacman::p_load(sf, terra, gstat, tmap, viridis, tidyverse)

2. Import data

rfstations <-
  read.csv("data/aspatial/RainfallStation.csv")
rainfall <-
  read.csv("data/aspatial/DAILYDATA_202402.csv")
rfdata <-
  read.csv('data/aspatial/DAILYDATA_202402.csv') %>%
  select(c(1,5)) %>%
  group_by(Station) %>%
  summarise (MONTHSUM = sum(Daily.Rainfall.Total..mm.)) %>%
  ungroup()
rfdata <- rfdata %>%
  left_join(rfstations)
rfdata_sf <- st_as_sf(rfdata,
                      coords= c("Longitude",
                                "Latitude"),
                      crs= 4326) %>%
  st_transform(crs = 3414)
mpsz2019 <- st_read(dsn ="data/geospatial",
                    layer = "MPSZ-2019") %>%
  st_transform(crs= 3134)

  `C:\Users\1\Desktop\ISSS608-Visual\Arieliscjh\ISSS608-VAA\In-class_Ex\In-class_Ex7\data\geospatial' 
  using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
Simple feature collection with 332 features and 6 fields
Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
Dimension:     XY
Bounding box:  xmin: 103.6057 ymin: 1.158699 xmax: 104.0885 ymax: 1.470775
Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
tmap_options(check.and.fix = TRUE)
tmap_mode("view")
tm_shape(mpsz2019) +
  tm_borders()+
tm_shape(rfdata_sf)+
  tm_dots(col= "MONTHSUM")
tmap_mode("plot")
grid <- terra::rast(mpsz2019,
                    nrows = 690,
                    ncols = 1075)
xy <- terra::xyFromCell(grid,
                        1:ncell(grid))
